Two-Way Binding in React MERN Stack Todo App
While React is known for its one-way data flow, there's a pattern called "controlled components" that simulates two-way binding behavior. Here's how it applies to your MERN stack todo application:

Concept:
In controlled components, the component's state dictates the value of the input field.
Any changes to the input field are reflected back to the component's state using event handlers (e.g., onChange).
